== '''Universal Changes''' ==
* '''{{clr|DR|Drive Gauge}} Appearance:''' if any amount of Drive gauge remains over the threshold (0/10000/20000/30000/40000/50000), the entire block of gauge will change color to make it easier to distinguish from an empty block
* '''{{clr|SA|Command Throw SA3/CA}}''' (Lily, Manon, Zangief): removed unnecessary block idle hitbox that allowed opponents to avoid the throw when landing from a jump
* '''{{clr|L|2LK}}''' (all characters): extended foot hurtbox that appears before active frames is now invincible to cross-up attacks
<br>

== '''Character Changes''' ==

=== '''C. Viper''' ===
* {{clr|L|j.LP}} / {{clr|H|j.HP}} no longer Force Stand when hitting a crouching opponent
* Lv.3 Focus Force (214[K]/{{clr|OD|[KK]}}) now deals +4 additional hitstun on {{clr|PC|Punish Counter}} like the uncharged versions
** Now KD +77, and crumple is +29 before opponent falls to the ground
<br>

=== '''Chun-Li''' ===
* Serenity Stream > {{clr|L|LP}} / {{clr|L|LK}} / {{clr|M|MK}} on Perfect Parry: removed some recovery frames immediately before her forced Stance Exit
** This reduces the total recovery on PP by 2f {{clr|L|(LP)}} / 5f {{clr|L|(LK)}} / 6f {{clr|M|(MK)}} and affects Perfect Parry disadvantage by the same amount
** This was done because despite being in a {{clr|PC|Punish Counter}} state, Chun-Li could block in the middle of her recovery animation on these frames. 
<br>

=== '''Dhalsim''' ===
* {{clr|SA|CA}} fixed a bug where the Drive Damage and Chip Damage were set to {{clr|SA|SA3}} levels when canceled into
** Drive Damage on Block: 7500 → 10000
** Chip Damage: 1000 → 1250
<br>

=== '''Elena''' ===
* Leopard Snap (236P~{{clr|L|6LK}}) Super Art gain 600 → 1000
* Boosted Leopard Snap (236P~6P~{{clr|L|6LK}} or {{clr|OD|236PP}}~{{clr|L|6LK}}) pushback on block reduced, and normalized the distance on block when used midscreen or in the corner
** 1st hit has less blowback on airborne opponents to make the 2nd hit more consistent in juggles
* Moon Glider (214P~6P) 2nd attack hitbox expanded forward
* {{clr|OD|OD Moon Glider}} ({{clr|OD|214PP}}) pushback on hit reduced, increased forward movement after the backwards sway
** More effective as a shimmy tool, leading to more consistent {{clr|PC|Punish Counter}} follow-ups
* {{clr|SA|SA1}} startup reduced 9f → 7f; total animation 96f → 94f; can now build {{clr|SA|Super}} gauge after landing this in a combo
** All airborne and air invuln frames shifted 2f earlier to compensate
<br>

=== '''Mai''' ===
* Forward Throw leaves Mai closer to a cornered opponent (can no longer walk back to shimmy after a dash)
* {{clr|H|5HP}} Drive Damage reduced 5000 → 4000
* Kachousen (236P) - Charged / {{clr|OD|Charged OD}} / {{clr|3|Flame}} versions build more Drive gauge for the defender when Parried and/or Perfect Parried
