=== '''Sagat''' ===
* {{clr|L|2LK}} pushback reduced on hit/block for more consistent hitconfirms
* {{clr|M|2MK}} Hit Advantage {{sf6-adv|VP|+4}} → {{sf6-adv|VP|+5}}; hitstun 25 → 26
** Gives a natural link to {{clr|L|5LP}}, a {{clr|PC|CH}} link to {{clr|L|5LK}}/{{clr|M|2MP}}, and a {{clr|DR|DR}}/{{clr|PC|PC}} link to itself at farther ranges
* {{clr|H|Tiger Monolith}} ({{clr|H|4HP}}) 1st hit active frames increased 2 → 3 (more consistent juggle tool, does not affect anti-air frames)
* {{clr|H|Charged HP Tiger Uppercut}} ({{clr|H|623[HP]}}) now gives the stronger cinematic hit up to the 3rd active frame instead of only frames 1-2; collision box expanded upward on active frames 1-2
** This slightly increases the max range of the strong hit and makes it more consistent in some high juggles
* {{clr|H|HK Tiger Knee}} ({{clr|H|236HK}}) expanded combo-only hitbox of 2nd hit upward to prevent it from whiffing when 1st hit connects (does not apply to "sweet spot" connect)
* {{clr|L|LK}}/{{clr|M|MK}} Tiger Nexus ({{clr|L|214LK}}/{{clr|M|214MK}}) increased pushback on hit; increased forward movement during startup; increased horizontal blowback on airborne hit
** Total range 1.56 → 1.66 ({{clr|L|214LK}}) / 1.86 → 1.96 ({{clr|M|214MK}})
** More consistent in grounded confirms (e.g. 3 lights > {{clr|L|214LK}}), while keeping juggle scenarios intact
* {{clr|L|Mighty Tiger}} (214K/{{clr|OD|KK}}~{{clr|L|6LK}}) increased pushback on hit; increased horizontal blowback on airborne hit
** If {{clr|L|214LK}}~{{clr|L|6LK}} is used from a 2-light confirm, opponent is in range for Throw or {{clr|L|2LK}}~{{clr|L|5LP}} mixup; does not work from new 3-light confirm
* {{clr|M|Greedy Tiger}} (214K/{{clr|OD|KK}}~{{clr|M|6MK}}) Drive Damage increased 6000 → 8000
* {{clr|H|Nova Tiger}} (214K/{{clr|OD|KK}}~{{clr|H|6HK}}) reduced pushback on block
** Can now throw opponents who back walk, but can no longer shimmy unless opponent delays throw tech at least 3f
<br>